HEADWORD: Colluvies
<hw>Col*lu"vi*es</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
collection of washings, dregs, offscourings, fr. <ets>colluere</ets> to
wash; <ets>col-</ets> + <ets>luere</ets> to wash.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A collection or gathering, as of pus, or rubbish, or odds and
ends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A medley; offscourings or rabble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colly</ent>⟦br⟧
